https://ridmik.com/about/ridmik/privacy:
Welcome to Ridmik. Your privacy matters to us.
Last Updated on: Oct 9, 2023
Ridmik ("Ridmik", "us", " our" or "we") is dedicated to protecting the
privacy rights of our users ("users" or "you"). This Privacy Policy (the " Policy")
describes the ways we collect, store, use, and secure the information that you
provide or we collect in connection with our websites and applications provided on any platform (collectively,
    the "Services"). Ridmik is operated by Ridmik Labs Limited
By accessing and/or using our Services, you are expressing that you have
read and fully understand the information you shared with us.
Please do NOT use or access the Services if you do not agree or
have any concerns to this Policy. If you have any questions,
concerns or requests about this Policy, you can contact us through
  the methods described at the end of this Policy.
The Legal Basis of Collecting and Processing the Information
Ridmik collect and process the information users provide in accordance
with one of the legal basis set out under General Data Protection Regulation
(GDPR) and other applicable laws, regulations, codes and principals.
The legal bases which we rely upon are described below:
Consent: The users have given consent for one or more specific purposes and authorized Ridmik to collect and process the information.
Contractual Necessity: When the data collecting and processing is necessary for the performance of a contract between users and Ridmik, or in order to take steps prior to entering the contract.
Legal Obligation: When the data collecting and processing is necessary for fulfilling a legal obligation to which the Ridmik is subject, such as the prevention of crime or fraud.
Vital Interests: When the data collecting and processing is necessary for protecting the vital interests of the users or of another person.
Public task: When the data collecting and processing is necessary for performing a task carried out in the public interest or as contained under the official authority given to Ridmik.
Legitimate Interests: When the data collecting and processing is necessary for the purpose of the legitimate interests pursued by Ridmik or by a third party, except when such interests are overridden by the interests or fundamental rights and freedoms of the users which require protection of personal data, especially where the data subject is a child.
The Purpose of Collecting the Information
The information are collected for the following purposes:
Creating accounts and allow users to access our applications and Services;
Understanding users' preferences, to enhance users' experiences and enjoyment by using our Services;
Sending the related information, including confirmations, invoices, technical notices, updates, push notifications, security alerts, support and administrative messages to the users;
Identifying and suggesting connections with other users;
Making an announcement of promotions, rewards, upcoming events, and other news about our Services;
Responding to users’ queries;
Sending targeted advertising, offers and other sponsored content based on the behaviors and preferences of users but exclude data concerning users’ personal health, medical and fitness condition;
Enabling the users to communicate with other users;
Conducting research, big data analytics and create reports for internal use;
Personalizing and providing users with better online experiences and customer support;
The Information We Collect and How We Use It
The information we collect depend on how you use our Services.
Information we collect automatically
While you are browsing Ridmik's Sites or
  using the applications, certain
  information may be logged automatically, such information including but not limited
  to your computer’s operating system, Internet Protocol (IP) address, access times,
  browser type and language and referring Web site addresses.
  We may use this information to monitor, develop and analyze
  your use of the Services. In addition, we may ask you to submit
  and we may process data that is personal to you, including
  but not limited to your name, profile photo, gender, age or
  birthday, interests, user names
  and e-mail and mailing addresses. We may use this
  information to create a user profile and provide
  you Services. We may use your email address to contact
  you about your experience with our Sites/Services
  and notify you about our latest news or promotions.
  Your gender and birthday may be used to analyze user
  trends and target certain promotions. Your mailing
  address may be used if we have merchandise or
  other physical promotional materials that we
  want to send to you. If you no longer wish to
  receive these types of promotional materials, you
  can contact us through the methods described at
  the end of this Policy and let us know you would
    like to opt-out of receiving promotional emails or notifications from us.
Mobile Analytics
We use mobile analytics tools to better understand the functionality of
  our Services on your device. This software may record information such
  as how often you use the Services, the events that occur within the Services,
  aggregated usage, performance data, and where the Services were downloaded
  from.
